INPUT: dirk_test1.i

PROBLEM:

Solve 2D heat equation u_t = u_xx + u_yy + f on [0,1]^2

Set u(x,t) = t*(x^2 + y^2) so that

u_t  = x^2+y^2
u_xx = 2t
u_yy = 2t

and therefore

u_t - u_xx - u_yy = x^2 + y^2 - 2t =: f

Integrate until end_time = 1.0 and set very small tolerances for nonlinear solves.

